Telephone number Postal code A combination of letters and numbers that designate a particular region or location used to deliver mail via postal system. Integer A number in a specified range that is not a fraction A number between two shown numbers, like '99' for a range of '1' to '100' Range of Integers The first and last elements in a sequence of numbers that are not fractions The first and last of a number sequence, like '1' and '4' for { 1, 2, 3, 4 } City/Province Region code A combination of letters and numbers that designate a particular region. Street address The local address, usually includes a number for a part of a street, a street name, and sometimes more specific identifiers like room or suite reference. Local part of an address that includes street name. Like '123 Main st.' Text Writing made of characters, symbols or sentences. Some letters and spaces. 'Like this text.' Text word A combination of characters or symbols without separators like spaces or punctuation marks. One word, like 'ThisIsOneWord' Time of day A point in time including specific hours and minutes, and maybe seconds. '11:00' is an hour before noon, '23:00' is an hour before midnight. Timestamp A point in time including a date and time of day in a standard format. For example, July 21, 1969, at 2:56 and 15 seconds UTC becomes '1969-07-21 02:26:15 +0000' A point in time, like when a person first stepped on the Moon at '1969-07-21 02:26:15' URL A Uniform Resource Locator, such as an address to a web page or image where a particular document may be found.
